FBIS3-36958 "drsov028_e_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Foreign Minister Pays Official Visit to Spain Maintains Opposition to Air Strikes LD0902211694 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1900 GMT 9 Feb 94 LD0902211694 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Russia and Ukraine, the two big Slav republics, maintain their total opposition to any kind of action by NATO forces against the Serbs in Bosnia. Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko, who has just made a speech in Madrid after his visit with Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana, repeated his view that air strikes could cause an escalation of the war. He particularly underlined the danger involved for the civilian population, as well as for the Blue Helmet contingents stationed in the area. [Begin Zlenko recording, in Spanish] I am very worried about the present situation in this region because the military contingent from my country is in Sarajevo, and you know that this situation makes us search for other solutions. [end recording]
